[The number of cases in Darfur continues to rise. One wonders about the delay in getting lab results; perhaps there was a delay in the specimens reaching Dakar. - Mod.JW

In the 1st report on this outbreak covered by ProMED-EAFR (see Yellow fever - Sudan: (Darfur) 20121103.28571503), there were a total of 84 suspected cases, including 32 deaths, reported in the districts of Azoom, Kass, Mershing, Nertiti, Nyala, Wadi Salih and Zalingei during the period 1-31 Oct 2012. The above reports increase the number of suspected cases to 266 with 85 fatalities reported from 20 localities in Sudan and mention the start of reports in the last week of September 2012.

Information on the epidemiologic investigations would be greatly appreciated, including dates of onset of cases along with epidemic curves.

For a map of Sudan, see the March 2012 map of Sudan available on Relief Web at http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/sudan.pdf. For the HealthMap/ProMED map of Sudan, see http://healthmap.org/promed/index.php?name=Sudan&p=96&g=&v=13.832,30.05,5,96. - Mod.MPP]
